N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. tit. 22, subtit. D, ch. IV, subch. A, Paternity Forms (Family Court Act Article 5), form 5-9 - Remand commitment (undertaking)

State Regulations
F. C.A. §§ 528, 533 Form 5-9
(Remand Commitment

Undertaking)
7/2003
FAMILY COURT OF THE STATE OF NEW
YORK
COUNTY OF
________
In the Matter of a Paternity Proceeding

Docket No. Petitioner, REMAND COMMITMENT
-against- (Undertaking)

Respondent. ________
TO ANY PEACE OFFICER OF THE STATE OF NEW
YORK AND TO THE SHERIFF of the JAIL OF ________ COUNTY: The above-named respondent having been
brought before this Court upon a petition filed under Article 5 of the Family

Court Act, seeking a declaration that said Respondent is the father of a
certain child born out of wedlock and other relief; AND the said Respondent having thereupon
been duly held for further proceedings to be held on, he is required to furnish
an undertaking in the sum of $ with sufficient surety approved by the Court, for his appearance on that date and in default thereof he is hereby committed
to the custody of the above-named Sheriff or Warden until said date unless
sooner discharged according to law; AND YOU ARE, THEREFORE, COMMANDED
forthwith to take charge of the above-named Respondent and deliver him into the
care and custody of the said Sheriff or Warden. ______________
Judge of the Family Court
____________
Docket No. (Prison) (Jail)
(County)
(City)
(Town) of
TO THE FAMILY COURT, COUNTY, This is to acknowledge receipt of the body
of committed hereto on the annexed Commitment under Article 5 of the Family

Court Act. Time: a.m. p. m. ______________
Sheriff or Warden
